2.3 Black Hole Termination Mechanism
The system triggers automatic termination when any of these conditions hold:
Extreme k-values: |k| > 15
Parameter breakdown: z > 2.0 OR R < 0.1 OR y > 3.0
Divergence detection: |n| > 10^10 (unrealistic system size)
Reserve depletion: R approaches zero for consecutive periods
Upon black hole activation:
Financial interpretation: Market crash, bank runs, currency collapse
Political interpretation: Government crisis, electoral upheaval, institutional breakdown
Model behavior: n_t reset to 10% of previous value (representing value destruction)

